The paper deals with coding schemes for communication channels, specifically broadcast channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the complexity of encoding and decoding, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions the use of polarization, which is a technique used in signal processing and could place it in cs.SI (Signal Processing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
